#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:58
msgid ""
"The :term:`focal length` setting controls the amount of zoom, i.e. the "
"amount of the scene which is visible all at once. Longer focal lengths "
"result in a smaller :abbr:`FOV (Field of View)` (more zoom), while short "
"focal lengths allow you to see more of the scene at once (larger "
":abbr:`FOV (Field of View)`, less zoom)."
msgstr ""
"此 :term:`焦距` 设置控制变焦量，即可见的所有场景的量。较长的焦距会导致较小的 :abbr:`FOV (视野)` "
"，而较短的焦距可以让您一次看到更多的场景（更大的 :abbr:`FOV (视野)` ，更少的变焦）。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:66
msgid ""
"Render of the same scene as above, but with a focal length of 210mm "
"instead of 35mm."
msgstr "呈现与上述相同的场景，但焦距为210mm，而不是35mm。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:70
msgid "Lens Unit"
msgstr "镜头尺寸"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:69
msgid ""
"The focal length can be set either in terms of millimeters or the actual "
":term:`Field of View` as an angle."
msgstr "焦距可以以毫米为单位，也可以以实际 :term:`视野` 为角度来设定。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:73
msgid "Orthographic"
msgstr "正交"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:75
msgid ""
"With *Orthographic* perspective objects always appear at their actual "
"size, regardless of distance. This means that parallel lines appear "
"parallel, and do not converge like they do with *Perspective*."
msgstr "使用 *正交* 查看对象时，无论距离如何，总是以实际大小显示。这以为着平行线视乎是平行的，并不像 *透视* 那样（近大远小）。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:80
msgid ""
"Render from the same camera angle as the previous examples, but with "
"orthographic perspective."
msgstr "与前面的例子相同的摄像机角度渲染，但使用的是正交视角。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:88
msgid "Orthographic Scale"
msgstr "正交比例"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:83
msgid "This controls the apparent size of objects in the camera."
msgstr "这个选项控制摄像机中物体的外观尺寸。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:85
msgid ""
"Note that this is effectively the only setting which applies to "
"orthographic perspective. Since parallel lines do not converge in "
"orthographic mode (no vanishing points), the lens shift settings are "
"equivalent to translating the camera in the 3D View."
msgstr "改变设置调整消失点。消失点指的是图像中平行线的位置。在这个例子中，最明显的消失点是铁路的尽头。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:91
msgid "Panoramic"
msgstr "全景"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:93
msgid ""
"Panoramic cameras are only supported in the Cycles Renderer. See "
":ref:`the Cycles documentation <cycles-panoramic-camera>`."
msgstr "全景相机仅在Cycles渲染引擎中受支持。请查阅 :ref:`Cycles文档 <cycles-panoramic-camera>` 。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:98
msgid "Shift"
msgstr "切移"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:100
msgid ""
"The *Shift* setting allows for the adjustment of *vanishing points*. "
"*Vanishing points* refer to the positions to which parallel lines "
"converge. In this example, the most obvious vanishing point is at the end"
" of the railroad."
msgstr "通过 *切移* 设置可以调整 *消失点* 。 *消失点* 是指平行线汇聚的位置。在实例中，最明显的消失点是在铁路的尽头。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:104
msgid "To see how this works, take the following examples:"
msgstr "要看看这是如何工作的，请查看下面的例子："

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:108
msgid "Render of a train track scene with a horizontal lens shift of 0.330."
msgstr "以0.330的水平镜头切移渲染火车铁轨的场景。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:112
msgid ""
"Render of a train track scene with a rotation of the camera object "
"instead of a lens shift."
msgstr "通过相机对象的旋转来渲染火车铁轨的场景，而不是镜头切移。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:114
msgid ""
"Notice how the horizontal lines remain perfectly horizontal when using "
"the lens shift, but do get skewed when rotating the camera object."
msgstr "可以注意到水平线在使用镜头切移时如何保持完美水平，但在旋转相机对象时确实会发生倾斜。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:117
msgid ""
"Using lens shift is equivalent to rendering an image with a larger "
":abbr:`FOV (Field of View)` and cropping it off-center."
msgstr "使用镜头切移等同于渲染具有较大 :abbr:`FOV (视域)` 的图像并将其偏离中心。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:124
msgid "Clipping"
msgstr "覆盖范围"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:128
msgid "Clip Start and End"
msgstr "起始与结束"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:127
msgid ""
"The interval in which objects are directly visible; Only objects within "
"the limits are rendered."
msgstr "对象直接可见的区间；只有范围内的对象被渲染。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:130
msgid ""
"For OpenGL display, setting clipping distances to limited values is "
"important to ensure sufficient rasterization precision. Ray tracing "
"renders do not suffer from this issue so much, and as such more extreme "
"values can safely be set."
msgstr "对于OpenGL显示，将覆盖范围设置为限制值对于确保足够的光栅化精度非常重要。光线跟踪渲染不会受到这个问题的影响，因此可以安全地设置更极端的值。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:135
msgid ""
"When *Limits* in the *Display* panel is enabled, the clip bounds will be "
"visible as two yellow connected dots on the camera line of sight."
msgstr "当 *显示* 面板中的 *限制* 被启用时，覆盖范围边界在摄像机视线上将显示为两个黄色链接的点。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:140
msgid ""
"Changing the clipping value can have a serious impact on render "
"performance. It is important to always set the *Start* and *End* values "
"to a safe distance that is both not too extreme, nor too small to have "
"the best possible render times."
msgstr ""
"更改覆盖范围的值可能会严重影响渲染性能。始终将 *开始* 和 *结束* "
"值设置为一个安全距离非常重要，想要得到最佳渲染时间，必须将这两个距离设置在合适的范围。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:146
msgid ":ref:`Blender Render Camera Clipping <camera-clipping>`."
msgstr ":ref:`Blender 渲染 覆盖范围 <camera-clipping>`."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:147
msgid ":doc:`3D View clipping </editors/3dview/properties/panels>`."
msgstr ":doc:`3D视图 覆盖范围 </editors/3dview/properties/panels>`."

