#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:164
msgid "Sensor size"
msgstr "传感器"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:163
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This setting is an alternative way to control the focal length, it is "
"useful to match the camera in Blender to a physical camera & lens "
"combination, e.g. for :doc:`motion tracking "
"</editors/movie_clip_editor/index>`."
msgstr ""
"此设置是控制焦距的一种替代方法，将Blender中的摄像机与物理相机和镜头组合（例如匹配用于 :doc:`运动跟踪 "
"</editors/movie_clip_editor/index>`）相匹配非常有用。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:168
msgid "Sensor Fit"
msgstr "传感器适配"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:167
msgid ""
"Option to control which dimension (vertical or horizontal) along which "
"field of view angle fits."
msgstr "可以选择控制视角适合哪个尺寸（垂直或水平）。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:171
msgid "Depth of Field"
msgstr "景深"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:175
#, fuzzy
msgid "Camera Depth of Field panel."
msgstr "摄像机景深面板。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:177
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Real-world cameras transmit light through a lens that bends and focuses "
"it onto the sensor. Because of this, objects that are a certain distance "
"away are in focus, but objects in front and behind that are blurred."
msgstr "真实世界的摄像机通过镜头传输光线，将其折射并聚焦到传感器上。因此，特定距离的物体才是焦点，而前后物体则是模糊的。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:181
msgid ""
"The area in focus is called the *focal point* and can be set using either"
" an exact value, or by using the distance between the camera and a chosen"
" object:"
msgstr "焦点区域称为 *焦点* ，可以使用精确值或通过使用摄像机和所选对象之间的距离进行设置："

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:186
msgid "Focus Object"
msgstr "焦点对象"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:185
msgid ""
"Choose an object which will determine the focal point. Linking an object "
"will deactivate the distance parameter. Typically this is used to give "
"precise control over the position of the focal point, and also allows it "
"to be animated or constrained to another object."
msgstr "选择一个聚焦的物体，聚焦对象后将关闭距离参数。通常这是用来精确控制焦点的位置，还可以使焦点移动或限制到另一个对象上。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:195
msgid "Distance"
msgstr "距离"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:189
msgid ""
"Sets the distance to the focal point when no *Focus Object* is specified."
" If *Limits* are enabled, a yellow cross is shown on the camera line of "
"sight at this distance."
msgstr "设置没有指定 *焦点对象* 时到焦点的距离。如果启用了 *限制* ，则在此距离的摄像机视线上会显示一个黄色十字。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:194
msgid ""
"Hover the mouse over the *Distance* property and press :kbd:`E` to use a "
"special *Depth Picker*. Then click on a point in the 3D View to sample "
"the distance from that point to the camera."
msgstr "当鼠标悬停在 *距离* 属性上，然后按 :kbd:`E` 可以使用特殊的 *深度选取器* 。然后点击三维视图中的一个点来采样从该点到摄像机的距离。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:199
msgid "High Quality"
msgstr "高质量"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:198
msgid ""
"In order for the viewport to offer an accurate representation of depth of"
" field (blur radius calculation), like a render, you must enable High "
"Quality. Without it, you may notice a difference in shading. (Grayed out "
"if not supported by the GPU)."
msgstr "为了使视图像渲染一样提供准确的景深（模糊半径计算），您必须启用“高质量”，你会注意到阴影表现的不同。（如果GPU不支持则改选项无效）。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:204
msgid "Viewport F-stop"
msgstr "光圈级数"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:202
msgid ""
"Controls the real-time focal blur effect used during sequencer or OpenGL "
"rendering and, when enabled, camera views in the 3D View. The amount of "
"blur depends on this setting, along with Focal Length and Sensor Size. "
"Smaller Viewport F-stop values result in more blur."
msgstr "控制在音序器或OpenGL渲染过程中使用的实时焦点模糊效果，以及在3D视图中启用相机视图时使用的实时焦点模糊效果。模糊量取决于此设置以及焦距和传感器尺寸。较小的视口光圈值会导致更多的模糊。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:209
msgid "Blades"
msgstr "刃型"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:207
msgid ""
"Add a number of polygonal *blades* to the blur effect, in order to "
"achieve a *bokeh effect* in the viewport. To enable this feature, the "
"blades must be set to at least 3 (3 sides, triangle)."
msgstr "在模糊效果中添加多个多边形 *刃型* ，以便在视口中实现 *散景效果* 。要启用此功能，刃型必须设置为至少3（三边，三角形）。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:213
msgid "The viewport bokeh effect with the blades set to 3."
msgstr "刃型的视角散景效果设置为3。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:217
msgid "Display"
msgstr "显示"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:221
#, fuzzy
msgid "Camera Display panel."
msgstr "摄像机显示面板。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:223
msgid "Limits"
msgstr "限制"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:224
msgid "Shows a line which indicates *Start* and *End Clipping* values."
msgstr "显示一条指示 *开始* 和 *结束剪切* 值的行。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:229
msgid "Mist"
msgstr "雾场"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:226
msgid ""
"Toggles viewing of the mist limits on and off. The limits are shown as "
"two connected white dots on the camera line of sight. The mist limits and"
" other options are set in the *World* panel, in the :doc:`Mist section "
"</render/blender_render/world/mist>`."
msgstr ""
"切换查看雾场的限制。限制在摄像机视线上显示为两个连接的白点。雾场的限制和其他选项在 *世界* 面板中的 :doc:`雾场 "
"</render/blender_render/world/mist>` 中进行设置。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:233
msgid "Camera view displaying safe areas, sensor and name."
msgstr "摄像机视图显示安全区域、传感器和名称。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:235
msgid "Sensor"
msgstr "触发器"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:236
msgid "Displays a dotted frame in camera view."
msgstr "在摄像机视图中打开或关闭虚线框显示。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:237
msgid "Name"
msgstr "名称"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:238
msgid "Toggle name display on and off in camera view."
msgstr "在摄像机视图中打开和关闭名称显示。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:240
msgid "Size"
msgstr "尺寸"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:240
msgid ""
"Size of the camera visualization in the 3D View. This setting has **no** "
"effect on the render output of a camera. The camera visualization can "
"also be scaled using the standard Scale :kbd:`S` transform key."
msgstr "3D视图中摄像机可视化的大小。此设置对摄像机的渲染输出 **没有** 影响。摄像机可视化也可以使用标准缩放 :kbd:`S` 键进行缩放。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:247
msgid "Passepartout"
msgstr "外边框"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:243
msgid "This option darkens the area outside of the camera's field of view."
msgstr "此选项会使摄像机视野外的区域变暗。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:247
msgid "Alpha"
msgstr "Alpha"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:246
msgid "Controls the transparency of the passepartout mask."
msgstr "控制外边框的透明度。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:250
msgid "Composition Guides"
msgstr "构图辅助线"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:252
msgid ""
"*Composition Guides* are available from the menu, which can help when "
"framing a shot. There are eight types of guides available:"
msgstr "此 *构图辅助线* 可从菜单中获得，这可以在构图时提供帮助。有八种类型的辅助线可用："

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:255
msgid "Center"
msgstr "中心"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:256
msgid "Adds lines dividing the frame in half vertically and horizontally."
msgstr "添加垂直和水平分割框架的线条。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:257
msgid "Center Diagonal"
msgstr "对角中心"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:258
msgid "Adds lines connecting opposite corners."
msgstr "添加连接对角的线。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/camera/object_data.rst:259
